nodes.bodyText:
In case that is the intended behaviour :-) After some simple refactoring I came to this if/else simplifcation:
int next = this.sequenceNumber + increment;
if (next > SEQUENCE_NUMBER_MAXIMUM) {
next -= SEQUENCE_NUMBER_MAXIMUM - 1;
} else if (next < 0) {
next = SEQUENCE_NUMBER_MAXIMUM - next * -1 + 1;
}
which is kinda weird... why an else? how could next become < 0? I guess only if you set a negative increment. But why would you do that? Is that possible? I just remove the else, and leave the if there.

